  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">George Thompson describes the convention in Union Village; S.S.F. [Stephen Symonds Foster] attacked church organizations and Abby [Kelly Foster] &quot;made a masterly (no mistressly) speech.&quot; Thompson received vociferous applause for his replies to a critic. Thompson closes the letter by saying: &quot;Can you put up with these epistles? If you can you shall hear more concerning the rambles of an Incendiary.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes, accompanying envelope with the delivery address: &quot;Messrs. Goodhue &amp; Co., New York City.&quot; With a notation in the lower left corner: &quot;For Miss A. W. Weston.&quot;</subfield>
